# Testing & QA

## After code changes

| Area changed | Minimum checks |
|--------------|----------------|
| JS/TS app code | `npm run lint` |
| TypeScript types | `npx tsc --noEmit` (if no `typecheck` script) |
| Expo config / deps | `npx expo-doctor` |
| Game logic / Firebase | Manual smoke test on device or emulator |
| Release build | Full checklist in [docs/release-workflow.md](docs/release-workflow.md) |

## Standard commands

```bash
cd jahw3-app
npm run lint
npx expo-doctor
```

Optional (when configured):

```bash
npm run typecheck
npm test
npx tsc --noEmit
```

## Manual device QA (core game loop)

Run on **physical device or emulator** with valid `.env`:

- App starts; Firebase/Firestore connects (startscreen status)
- Enter player name; navigate to lobby
- Create or join lobby; ready system works
- Host starts game; all players redirect to game screen
- Draw magic card; card modal and timers behave correctly
- Voting and reaction phases complete without crash
- Card gallery loads cards from configured data source

## Before commit

All **available** automated checks must pass. Do not commit if `npm run lint` reports errors.

Do not mark manual QA items complete in `project.md` until verified on device.
